title: For Sale:  Benelli M4 Tactical Shotgun with Upgrades
postcontent:
This is the Benelli M4 Tactical shotgun (12 gauge), the civilian version of the US Military's M1014 Combat Shotgun. 

I bought this shotgun for home defense from Gander Mountain. It has had ~25 rounds through it, so is basically new - a safe queen. It functions flawlessley. I need to sell to pay down some debts.

This shotgun comes stock with a OEM black pistol grip stock - that is too long by a mile. I upgraded the stock with a Mesa Tactical pistol grip stock with a Limbsaver recoil pad (in OD green) and matching forend. This stock lets you put in spacers to adjust length of pull and is an essential upgrade. I also had installed an extended mag tube (to increase capacity to 7 shells). The mag tube is titanium and made by Carrier Comp and is considered the best of all of the available upgrade mag extensions and wait times for these are 3-6 months. It had a Wolff upgraded spring and follower installed with the extension. Stock on the gun was a small button bolt release that is not suitable for home defense/stress situations. I had a GG&G tactical bolt release pad installed, which makes the shotgun combat/HD-ready. Last is an Esstac Shotgun Card/Side saddle. This is way more versitile than the plastic sidesaddle shell carriers since they are easily removed and replaced to switch out ammo type (slugs, buck, etc). All in all, it is one of the best HD/Combat shotguns you can have in the present confuguration.

Gander Mountain price                        $1800
Ohio Tax (~7%)                                 $125
CarrierComp Titanium Mag Extension    $200
Mesa Urbino Stock (Limbsaver)             $150
GG&G Extended Bolt Release                $120
Esstac Shotgun Card                            $15
Total if purchased                             ~$2400

I am asking a firm $2000 cash. No trades, please don't offer any. I will meet at Blackwing Shooting center and pay the range fee so you can shoot a couple rounds - if you are serious.

Transaction:
- You must be an Ohio resident with a valid Ohio drivers license (must present for sale) 
- You must be legally entitled to purchase a firearm (responding is affermation)
- I will complete a bill of sale/transfer
- Sale is cash only
- I may consider an out of state purchase (FFL to FFL only), but you will need to pay all FFL transfer and shipping/insurance fees. Sale would be via cashiers check in this case.

title: For Sale/Trade:  2001 Ford F250 Super Duty 7.3 Turbo Diesel Trade for guns and ammo
postcontent:
Up for sale or trade is my 2001 Ford F250 Super Duty with the unstoppable 7.3 Turbo Diesel in it.

The truck is in great condition and has less than 200k miles, which for a Diesel is just fantastic, it was a fleet vehicle for most of its life and its job was to carry those construction lights you see set up, deliver tools and as well as diesel to other trucks, it was never ran for hours on end and had a pretty easy going life for a work truck. Has manual everything, windows, doors, seat, so nothing is electric to mess up or be over complicated.

The good;

Truck has low miles and has been well taken care of, all fluid changes on time since it was driven off the lot, recently changed the fuel filter

Had an alternator put in that is less than 6 months old at this point

Air gets ice cold fast, and heat gets as hot as you want just as quickly.

This is my daily driver at this point (about 40 miles a week, 90% are highway)

Has a big metal bumper and towing package so you can hook whatever you want to it and it will pull it, boats, cars, toys, houses.

Large chest in the back for putting stuff in

Spare fuel tank with electric pump, all in working order, at one point I filled it up when I was able to snag some very cheap diesel but don't really use it since then.


The bad

Still has its ugly shortbus yellow paint job from working for the city, a bit of decal is still on the truck and it could use some cleaning up.

Key to the chest is lost, its unlocked so it can still be opened and closed, just not locked. I think it would be 10$ or so for new locking cylinders

Both rear tires will need to be replaced in the next year, the tires are in good shape but the tread has been worn down quite a bit.

The truck chugs at times, I am not sure if this is the fuel pump or possibly the cps since those failed on these every so often, either way I have been too lazy to replace either since my big jack stands and jack are under a whole bunch of crap in the garage, and I am too fat to fit under the truck while its just stting. I do happen to have a spare CPS sensor, it will come with the truck and for anyone who isn't lazy and fat will be a 10 min job to replace

Ding in the front of the hood and the grill, could be fixed up but isn't really a big deal at all

The rest of the body is straight and good to go aside from normal dinks and such over it's life, but nothing really bad as it never did a huge amount of work.

My plan for it was actually to take all the guts out of the truck completely leaving it a shell, and stuffing them into an old ford bronco body and building everything up from there, unfortunately I don't know if I am getting too old and fat too fast but I really just have lost the care to do that, I am going to sell this truck along with my other truck and probably pick up a "luxury" suv or crossover, something for me to simply cruise in. Though I suspect at some point I will cave and buy another diesel, after driving them for so many years you can't really take the quiet of gasser motors.

Anyway thats most of the info I can think of offhand, if you have any other questions or want to see the truck just let me know

And unfortunately the 7000 is not negotiable that is what I will accept in cash for this truck at any given time, if I decide to accept less then I will alter the ad to show it, but if I don't get the truck sold before its registration runs out, I will probably just park it in the backyard and wonder what to do with it for a few years.

Merry Christmas.
